jxcss
Class SAXCSSDocumentHandler

java.lang.Object
  jxcss.SAXCSSDocumentHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.w3c.css.sac.DocumentHandler
public class SAXCSSDocumentHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.w3c.css.sac.DocumentHandler

This class implements the org.w3c.css.sac.DocumentHandler by generating appropriate SAX events for each parser event. This class is the workhorse of the JXCSS framework.
The following two properties control the operation of the class:

  • org.xml.sax.ContentHandler contentHandler: This mandatory property defines the receiver of the SAX events generated in response to each CSS parser event.
  • java.lang.String namespacePrefix: This optional property controls the namespace prefix to be output in association with the JXCSS URI (xcss/1.0). When unspecified, the default prefix is "xcss";

Generated SAX events conform to the XCSS DTD which models the structure of a CSS stylesheet as defined by the W3C's Level-2 DOM.
